  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "*Title*: *Envoy core dumps with tracing.random_sampling enabled*\r\n\r\n*Description*:\r\nUsing latest Envoy proxy with Istio I am using runtime { tracing.random_sampling = 100 } to enable 1% traces sampled. \r\nThe expectation is that if the incoming request is not otherwise traced, 1% \r\nof the requests would be traced, per runtime_Config \r\n\r\nThis is my runtime configuration.\r\n```\r\nroot@istio-ingress-cdb9cc587-dhdnk:/etc/istio/proxy# find rt \r\nrt \r\nrt/tracing \r\nrt/tracing/random_sampling \r\nroot@istio-ingress-cdb9cc587-dhdnk:/etc/istio/proxy# cat \r\nrt/tracing/random_sampling \r\n# per 10000 of requests that will be randomly traced. \r\n# This runtime control is specified in the range 0-10000 and defaults to \r\n10000. \r\n# Thus, trace sampling can be specified in 0.01% increments. \r\n100 \r\n```\r\n\r\n*Call Stack*:\r\nWhen I enabled sampling at the edge (istio ingress), I get the following core dump \r\n```\r\n#0  0x00007f418039e269 in raise (sig=11) at \r\n../sysdeps/unix/sysv/linux/pt-raise.c:35 \r\n#1  0x0000000000ec280a in Envoy::SignalAction::sigHandler (sig=11, \r\ninfo=0x7f417c006430, context=0x7f417c006300) \r\n     at external/envoy/source/exe/signal_action.cc:39 \r\n#2  <signal handler called> \r\n#3  0x00000000009fee01 in \r\nEnvoy::Http::ConnectionManagerImpl::ActiveStream::encodeHeaders \r\n(this=0x29f3e00, filter=0x0, headers=..., end_stream=true) \r\n     at external/envoy/source/common/http/conn_manager_impl.cc:921 \r\n#4  0x0000000000a009b2 in \r\nEnvoy::Http::ConnectionManagerImpl::ActiveStreamDecoderFilter::encodeHeaders(std::unique_ptr<Envoy::Http::HeaderMap, \r\nstd::default_delete<Envoy::Http::HeaderMap> >&&, bool) (this=0x2a361c0, \r\nheaders=<unknown type in /usr/local/bin/envoy, CU 0x4162ad0, DIE 0x41cd059>, \r\n     end_stream=true) at \r\nexternal/envoy/source/common/http/conn_manager_impl.cc:1289 \r\n```\r\n\r\nThe issue was the active_span_ member variable is un-initialized. After I \r\nfixed that error in my fork things moved forward. ",
